The Wiper party top leadership is now demanding that the opposition National Super Alliance gives them an assurance that their party leader Kalonzo Musyoka will fly the coalitions flag in 2022. Speaking after a meeting at Stone Athi Resort in Machakos county Thursday evening, the leaders including former Machakos Senator Johnstone Muthama at the same time defended their leader against claims that his failure to show up at the Uhuru Park grounds for the swearing in of NASA leader Raila Odinga portrayed him as a sell-out. The development coming in at a time when the affiliate parties of the NASA coalition are holding separate meetings with rumours rife of each plotting to go it alone come 2022 